    a3: 'Wychwood\'s mix of heritage homes and renovated properties creates a two-tier refrigerator problem profile that our technicians encounter on every service day in this neighbourhood. In older Wychwood homes with original or older-replacement refrigerators, the top two calls are dirty condenser coils and thermostat failure. Condenser coils in older models that have not been cleaned in years become thickly coated with dust, causing the fridge to run constantly and feel warm inside. Coil cleaning ($100-$150) is an immediate fix. Thermostat failure on older models causes food to freeze in the fresh food compartment or the freezer to warm up, and thermostat replacement ($150-$250) resolves it reliably. In renovated Wychwood homes with newer LG and Samsung units, the most common complaints are ice maker failures and door seal wear. LG French door units from 2014-2019 may also have linear compressor issues, and we always check the recall first. Door seal wear is notably common in Wychwood because the neighbourhood has a high proportion of home offices and work-from-home residents who open the fridge frequently throughout the day. Nika Appliance Repair, serving Wychwood since 2017.',
    q4: 'How does same-day refrigerator repair work in Wychwood?',
    a4: 'Same-day service in Wychwood is straightforward because our technicians work the Midtown and west-end corridor daily, covering Wychwood alongside Hillcrest, Dovercourt, and Christie Pits. Call (437) 524-1053 before noon for a same-day afternoon appointment. When you call, describe the problem and give us the brand and approximate age of the fridge. For LG models, the serial number allows a recall check before the technician arrives. We work in all Wychwood property types: detached heritage homes, coach houses, and semi-detached conversions. Parking and access in Wychwood are generally good. On arrival, the $119 diagnostic identifies the fault and a written quote follows immediately. Condenser coil cleaning and start relay replacement are quick jobs completed in under an hour. Thermostat replacement is about 45 minutes. Ice maker assembly replacement and water inlet valve installs are also typically same-day. Our hours are Monday-Friday 8am-8pm, Saturday 9am-6pm, Sunday 10am-5pm. Every repair is backed by a 90-day parts and labour warranty. Nika Appliance Repair, serving Wychwood since 2017.',
    q5: 'What should I prepare before the refrigerator technician arrives in Wychwood?',
    a5: 'Getting ready before the visit helps our Wychwood technician complete the repair efficiently. First, find the model number and serial number label inside the fridge, on the left side wall near the top or along the door frame. For LG models, the serial number is used immediately for the linear compressor recall check. For older models, the model number helps confirm the correct thermostat or start relay part. Second, pull the fridge away from the wall or clear the space around it. Wychwood heritage kitchens are sometimes narrow with the fridge set close to a wall or cabinetry. Getting 18-24 inches of clearance behind the unit allows access to rear-mounted condenser coils and the power supply. Third, sweep or vacuum around and under the fridge. In older Wychwood homes with original hardwood floors and plaster walls, dust accumulates under the fridge rapidly and can scatter during the repair. A quick sweep takes two minutes. Fourth, if the fridge is not cooling, move temperature-sensitive food to a cooler in advance. Fifth, note when the problem started and any sounds you have observed. A clicking sound every few minutes points to the start relay. Frost on the inner back wall of the fridge section points to a defrost heater or thermostat issue. Nika Appliance Repair, serving Wychwood since 2017.'
